{"serial": "09065", "department_serial": 3, "code": "GS2152", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Famous Classical Music and Score Music Appreciation", "ch": "經典古典音樂與電影配樂之賞析"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["CHEN,HUI-CHUAN"], "ch": ["陳慧娟"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 1, "session": ["5", "6"]}, "loc": {"building": "O", "room": "122"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "通識教育中心", "en": "General Education Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 33, "selected": 49, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "由耳熟能詳的電影切入，帶領學生走進古典音樂的殿堂，讓學生了解古典音樂不是那麼難以親近或無法理解，會發現原來許多好聽的知名電影的配樂都是來自於古典音樂。透過課堂的講授和音樂的聆聽導讀，讓同學了解到一部好電影，除了需具備\n引人入勝的故事情節之外，能增加影像戲劇張力(如：緊張懸疑、激烈衝突、悲愴悽苦、英雄氣概、恬適安詳、抒情浪漫等)和鋪陳故事情節的電影配樂亦扮演功不可沒的角色。讓學生理解到音樂、影像與敘述性的故事的多方結合之下，可以讓電\n影情節和影像變得更鮮明動人和更有戲劇張力。當然，也會讓學生了解各種樂器的演奏原理、音質特色和相關著名曲目，才更能清楚掌握為何採用該樂器作為主要的配樂樂器。", "en": "Starting with familiar movies, students are led into the palace of classical music, allowing students to understand that classical music is not so inaccessible or incomprehensible. They will discover that the soundtracks of many well-known and enjoyable movies come from classical music. Through classroom lectures and music listening guides, students can understand that a good movie requires\nIn addition to the fascinating storyline, the film soundtrack that can increase the dramatic tension of the image (such as tension and suspense, fierce conflict, pathos, heroism, tranquility, lyrical romance, etc.) and lay out the storyline also plays an indispensable role. Let students understand that the multiple combinations of music, images and narrative stories can make movies\nThe scenes and images become more vivid and dramatic. Of course, students will also be able to understand the playing principles, sound quality characteristics and related famous repertoire of various musical instruments, so that they can better understand why this instrument is used as the main soundtrack instrument."}, "outline": {"ch": "1. 認識古典音樂與電影配樂\n2. 著名電影配樂家及其作品欣賞\n3. 巴洛克時期的電影配樂\n4. 古典時期的電影配樂\n5. 浪漫樂派時期的電影配樂\n6. ⼆⼗世紀⾳樂時期的電影配樂", "en": "1. Understand classical music and film scores\n2. Appreciation of famous film composers and their works\n3. Film scores from the Baroque period\n4. Film scores from the classical period\n5. Film scores from the Romantic period\n6. Film scores in the 20th century musical period"}, "textbook": {"ch": "指定教科書：陳慧娟、李和莆、吳佩蓉，「音樂賞析–西洋古典篇」，國立空中大學出\n版，2017/06/01。", "en": "指定教科書：陳慧娟、李和莆、吳佩蓉，「音樂賞析–西洋古典篇」，國立空中大學出\n版，2017/06/01。"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100%", "en": "100%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授", "en": ["Lecture"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "出席率與課堂參與度(20％)。\n專題研究報告 (40 ％ )： 至少 4 頁 A4 (14點標楷體) 的報告，交紙本及電子檔，二選\n一。(1) 觀看一部電影，找出那些背景音樂 (古典音樂為佳) 是出自哪位作家的第幾號作\n品？出現時間？主要樂器和演奏型態為何？所營造的劇情氛圍為何？ (2)音樂會欣賞心得\n報告 (須附曲目單或入場票卷)。\n分組報告(40％)：交紙本及電子檔 ，二選一 (電影配樂曲目介紹為佳) 。(1) 電影配樂曲目\n介紹 (古典音樂為佳) ： (i) 電影名稱及簡要說明、(ii) 配樂曲目介紹 、(iii) 音樂特色與配\n樂原因、(iv) 感想心得。(2) 古典音樂作家及其曲目介紹。附註：分組報告題目不能與任\n一組員的專題研究報告類似。", "en": "Attendance and class participation (20％).\nSpecial research report (40％)\nGroup report (40％)"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期下午三點~四點", "en": "Monday 15:00~16:00"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "補充教學影片", "en": "Off-line learning material"}, "domain": {"ch": "人文與思想領域", "en": "人文與思想領域"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "邏輯與創新", "rating": "(0)無", "assesments": ["無"]}, {"competencies": "多元與溝通", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "美感與鑑賞", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "關懷與實踐", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "", "rating": "(0)", "assesments": ["No assessment"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Ex